pageContext.claim: “Well, I never thought it would go smoothly. Venezuela hasn't gone smoothly since it became a socialist or worse-than-that country. So I never expected anything to go smoothly. We'll see what happens with Venezuela.”
pageContext.analysis: By all accounts, Trump expected the Venezuelan government to quickly fall after increased pressure from the United States. On May 1, 2019, Trump confidently cited "rumors" that President Nicolas Maduro had come close to leaving Venezuela.
